-- Argentina to send govt officials to meet mediator in debt case
-- By Sarah Marsh
-- Thu Jul 03, 2014 07:25PM EDT
-- None



BUENOS AIRES, July 3 (Reuters) - The U.S. court-appointed mediator in Argentina's battle with holdout investors in its debt said on Thursday the country's lawyers had confirmed that a group of government officials would travel to New York to meet him on July 7.

